    <h3>Our Spiritual and Community Services</h3>
    <p>
      The Church offers a wide range of spiritual, educational, and community services 
      to support the faithful and strengthen the Ethiopian Orthodox community in Belgium.
    </p>

    <h3>Spiritual Services</h3>

    <h4>1. Divine Liturgy (Qidase)</h4>
    <p>Regular Sunday and feast-day liturgies.</p>

    <h4>2. Sacraments</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Baptism</li>
      <li>Holy Communion</li>
      <li>Confession</li>
      <li>Matrimony</li>
      <li>Unction of the Sick</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Prayer & Fasting Programs</h4>
    <p>Weekly prayers, fasting seasons, and special gatherings.</p>

    <h3>Educational Services</h3>

    <h4>1. Sunday School</h4>
    <p>Teaching children the Bible, hymns, and Orthodox faith.</p>

    <h4>2. Youth Ministry</h4>
    <p>Programs for teenagers and young adults.</p>

    <h4>3. Bible Study & Catechism</h4>
    <p>Classes for adults and new believers.</p>

    <h3>Community Services</h3>

    <h4>1. Family Support</h4>
    <p>Counseling, home visits, and assistance.</p>

    <h4>2. Charity & Social Support</h4>
    <p>Helping the poor, sick, and refugees.</p>

    <h4>3. Cultural Activities</h4>
    <p>Celebrations of Ethiopian traditions and heritage.</p>

